<h1>Commitment Term</h1>
<p>Between the organization [ORGANIZATION NAME] and the undersigned participant/user.</p>

<h3>1. Purpose</h3>
<p>This Commitment Term sets out responsibilities, conditions, and guidelines for participation/use of services, systems, or activities provided by [ORGANIZATION NAME].</p>

<h3>2. Participant/User Obligations</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Comply with internal rules, policies, and applicable laws.</li>
    <li>Use provided resources ethically, responsibly, and securely.</li>
    <li>Protect access credentials and do not share them with third parties.</li>
    <li>Respect the confidentiality of any information accessed.</li>
    <li>Promptly report security incidents, misuse, or irregularities.</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Organization Obligations</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Provide guidance, support channels, and resources necessary for proper use.</li>
    <li>Adopt reasonable information security and data protection measures.</li>
    <li>Handle reported incidents with diligence and transparency.</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. Confidentiality and Data Protection</h3>
<p>Both parties agree to keep sensitive information confidential. The processing of personal data will follow applicable laws (e.g., LGPD/GDPR) and the organization’s privacy policies.</p>

<h3>5. Term and Termination</h3>
<p>This term is effective on the date of signature/acceptance and remains valid while the relationship lasts. It may be terminated upon breach of its clauses or by either party upon notice.</p>

<h3>6. Compliance</h3>
<p>The participant/user declares to have read, understood, and agreed to this term and the organization’s applicable policies.</p>

